latestPosts.caption:
One message that truly stayed with me came from someone in Calgary, Canada. A woman wrote to us saying her 95-year-old great-grandmother wanted to celebrate what might be her last birthday. She said, ‘If this ends up being my final meal, I’ll be proud it was here.’ That absolutely broke me. When she arrived, she was surrounded by four generations of her family. Watching her dine with such joy and dignity in a place I helped build was one of the most moving moments of my life,” says our cover star @vikaskhannagroup in a candid conversation with GlobalSpa

“Every single time we present a cheque on the table, we also give a gift to our guests. This idea was conceived as a very simple notion: that when we used to go to our grandmothers’ houses, we were always given something to keep in our pockets. It could be a small souvenir, money, a small gift, or a small idol of God. That has been the essence of Bungalow: that you feel you are visiting home,” says our cover star @vikaskhannagroup in a candid conversation with GlobalSpa
